00:09:40,820 --> 00:09:44,700
[Air China Inner Mongolia]

147
00:09:51,520 --> 00:09:52,400
Miss, let me help you.

148
00:09:53,240 --> 00:09:53,800
Thank you!

149
00:10:00,220 --> 00:10:01,260
[ID Card]

150
00:10:13,780 --> 00:10:15,380
[Bones of a Great Man]

151
00:10:29,340 --> 00:10:33,060
[Six months later]

152
00:10:34,060 --> 00:10:38,700
[Shanghai]

153
00:10:43,260 --> 00:10:47,060
[I love Shanghai]

154
00:10:52,440 --> 00:10:54,160
Your mom asked me yesterday

155
00:10:54,680 --> 00:10:56,520
if you have a boyfriend.

156
00:10:56,880 --> 00:10:58,680
I felt too embarrassed to tell her

157
00:10:59,040 --> 00:11:01,120
that you've wasted half a year

158
00:11:01,240 --> 00:11:02,560
dating a chemistry professor

159
00:11:02,560 --> 00:11:04,440
who's in Germany online!

160
00:11:05,480 --> 00:11:06,880
We're not dating online.

161
00:11:08,200 --> 00:11:09,440
Oh, sure it's not!

162
00:11:10,480 --> 00:11:12,640
Then why does it take you so long

163
00:11:12,760 --> 00:11:13,480
to reply to his emails?

164
00:11:13,640 --> 00:11:14,400
Why is that?

165
00:11:15,200 --> 00:11:16,640
The format and contents

166
00:11:16,760 --> 00:11:17,880
of his emails

167
00:11:17,880 --> 00:11:19,160
are always so formal.

168
00:11:19,320 --> 00:11:20,320
You'll understand when you see them.

169
00:11:20,440 --> 00:11:21,800
I have no choice but to reply carefully.

170
00:11:24,120 --> 00:11:25,880
A friend of mine wants to read them.

171
00:11:27,160 --> 00:11:27,960
A friend of mine

172
00:11:28,040 --> 00:11:29,880
thinks they are too boring to share with others.

173
00:11:33,680 --> 00:11:35,000
How old is he exactly?

174
00:11:36,360 --> 00:11:37,320
I've never asked.

175
00:11:37,920 --> 00:11:38,760
How old did he look?

176
00:11:40,040 --> 00:11:41,480
Late 20s?

177
00:11:44,280 --> 00:11:45,680
That's a dangerous age.

178
00:11:45,960 --> 00:11:47,240
It's hard to say whether he's married or not.

179
00:11:48,000 --> 00:11:48,880
In that case,

180
00:11:49,040 --> 00:11:50,440
everybody who's over 18 is dangerous.

181
00:11:52,000 --> 00:11:53,520
But

182
00:11:53,920 --> 00:11:55,640
the two of you are in different countries.

183
00:11:56,040 --> 00:11:57,640
How are you supposed to develop your relationship?

184
00:11:59,280 --> 00:12:01,760
I say, you should give up.

185
00:12:03,560 --> 00:12:04,640
Am I wrong?

186
00:12:04,800 --> 00:12:06,360
Don't tell me you'll want to be in a platonic love for the rest of your life!

187
00:12:11,520 --> 00:12:14,200
Actually, he's in Xi'an right now.

188
00:12:16,560 --> 00:12:17,440
He came back?

189
00:12:21,200 --> 00:12:22,400
For you?

190
00:12:23,000 --> 00:12:23,800
I told you he's on a

191
00:12:23,960 --> 00:12:25,000
business trip.

192
00:12:26,520 --> 00:12:27,560
I'm not finished yet!

193
00:12:29,880 --> 00:12:31,400
What else?

194
00:12:34,320 --> 00:12:35,240
I'll go on a business trip

195
00:12:35,400 --> 00:12:36,800
to Xi'an this weekend!

196
00:12:40,520 --> 00:12:41,880
And that relates to me how?

197
00:12:42,000 --> 00:12:43,480
Of course it does!

198
00:12:43,880 --> 00:12:45,320
Don't you think it's too coincidental?

199
00:12:45,440 --> 00:12:46,840
Isn't it destiny?

200
00:12:47,320 --> 00:12:48,360
Would you like to go with me?

201
00:12:50,480 --> 00:12:51,080
Let me break it down for you.

202
00:12:51,760 --> 00:12:53,200
You only need to buy a flight ticket.

203
00:12:53,360 --> 00:12:54,280
You don't need to pay for the hotel,

204
00:12:54,480 --> 00:12:55,160
since you'll be staying with me.

205
00:12:56,240 --> 00:12:57,400
Take it as a trip with me!

206
00:12:57,960 --> 00:12:58,720
At the same time,

207
00:12:58,880 --> 00:13:01,080
you can go see that "online friend"

208
00:13:01,280 --> 00:13:02,560
you've been communicating with via email!

209
00:13:04,280 --> 00:13:06,200
I may not have time.

210
00:13:13,000 --> 00:13:14,880
I need to check my work schedule.

211
00:13:17,520 --> 00:13:18,720
I'm leaving next Monday morning.

212
00:13:18,920 --> 00:13:20,200
You still have time to book a ticket.

213
00:13:51,980 --> 00:14:01,740
[Mail   To: Zhousheng Chen   From: Shi Yi]

214
00:13:53,600 --> 00:13:55,440
I happen to be going on a business trip

215
00:13:55,880 --> 00:13:57,200
to Xi'an next week.

216
00:13:58,080 --> 00:13:59,240
If you like,

217
00:13:59,800 --> 00:14:00,720
we can meet.

218
00:14:01,800 --> 00:14:02,560
Shi Yi.

219
00:14:16,500 --> 00:14:21,020
[Xi'an]

220
00:14:56,400 --> 00:14:57,360
I came unannounced.

221
00:14:58,080 --> 00:14:59,000
Surprised?

222
00:15:01,760 --> 00:15:03,280
I invited you to come back.

223
00:15:03,440 --> 00:15:04,760
Why would I be surprised?

224
00:15:17,400 --> 00:15:18,880
They invited you to a seminar

225
00:15:19,920 --> 00:15:21,520
but placed you in such a small place?

226
00:15:26,000 --> 00:15:27,640
Is this place small?

227
00:15:28,160 --> 00:15:29,840
I requested this room.

228
00:15:30,000 --> 00:15:30,960
It's only five-minute walk

229
00:15:31,120 --> 00:15:32,280
to the lab.

230
00:15:32,440 --> 00:15:33,400
It's a big timesaver.

231
00:15:34,920 --> 00:15:36,080
I know you don't care

232
00:15:36,240 --> 00:15:37,400
about these things,

233
00:15:38,680 --> 00:15:40,600
but as an associate professor,

234
00:15:40,760 --> 00:15:42,040
you should have some standards.

235
00:15:45,080 --> 00:15:47,000
The wealth we own is intangible.

236
00:15:48,440 --> 00:15:49,760
Don't lecture me

237
00:15:49,920 --> 00:15:51,560
about how the wealth of knowledge is above all.

238
00:15:52,160 --> 00:15:53,760
Every equipment in the lab

239
00:15:53,960 --> 00:15:55,000
costs at least 10 million Yuan.

240
00:15:55,400 --> 00:15:57,040
The reagent we've been using lately

241
00:15:57,200 --> 00:15:58,640
is hundreds of times the price of gold.

242
00:16:01,560 --> 00:16:02,840
Since you are that rich,

243
00:16:05,680 --> 00:16:07,320
you should prepare a big red envelope

244
00:16:08,080 --> 00:16:09,280
for the groom then.

245
00:16:10,160 --> 00:16:10,560
Here.

246
00:16:13,720 --> 00:16:15,200
What's this?

247
00:16:15,520 --> 00:16:16,640
Are you getting married?

248
00:16:17,620 --> 00:16:19,540
[Bridegroom: Zhou Wenchuan   Bride: Tong Jiaren]

249
00:16:18,400 --> 00:16:19,280
Your brother is.

250
00:16:22,960 --> 00:16:23,560
Surprised?

251
00:16:25,640 --> 00:16:26,760
Nope.

252
00:16:26,960 --> 00:16:28,240
Nothing is impossible.

253
00:16:29,080 --> 00:16:29,920
What about you?

254
00:16:32,160 --> 00:16:32,840
What do you mean?

255
00:16:33,080 --> 00:16:34,880
When will you meet with the fiancee

256
00:16:35,080 --> 00:16:35,960
your mom arranged for you?

257
00:16:37,880 --> 00:16:38,840
I don't have time.

258
00:16:41,640 --> 00:16:43,240
Do you lack time

259
00:16:43,400 --> 00:16:44,560
or do you lack courage?

260
00:16:45,320 --> 00:16:46,800
I really don't have the time.

261
00:16:49,720 --> 00:16:50,800
Let's talk when we get back.

262
00:16:53,040 --> 00:16:53,800
Suit yourself.

263
00:16:59,740 --> 00:17:02,140
[Lay a foundation for the sustainable development of students]

264
00:17:02,720 --> 00:17:04,800
It's such a strange year.

265
00:17:05,640 --> 00:17:08,640
Three years' worth of rain

266
00:17:08,880 --> 00:17:10,359
all came this year.

267
00:17:11,079 --> 00:17:13,040
It doesn't rain much in Shanghai, though.

268
00:17:14,000 --> 00:17:16,599
The rain all goes from the south to the north.

269
00:17:17,839 --> 00:17:19,120
Are you from Shanghai?

270
00:17:19,320 --> 00:17:19,960
Yes.

271
00:17:20,440 --> 00:17:22,120
Have you come to Xi'an for a business trip?

272
00:17:22,680 --> 00:17:23,320
They are on a business trip.

273
00:17:23,440 --> 00:17:24,520
I just took this chance to visit home.

274
00:17:27,080 --> 00:17:28,080
That's the ancient city wall over there.

275
00:17:28,560 --> 00:17:29,400
You know,

276
00:17:29,600 --> 00:17:30,680
there are many

277
00:17:30,880 --> 00:17:32,040
famous attractions in Xi'an.

278
00:17:32,200 --> 00:17:33,240
You girls can go for a tour

279
00:17:33,400 --> 00:17:34,600
after the interview.

280
00:17:36,680 --> 00:17:37,480
Young man,

281
00:17:37,640 --> 00:17:39,080
you should be a good host

282
00:17:39,280 --> 00:17:40,600
and bring them around!

283
00:17:41,720 --> 00:17:43,040
Yes! You are right!

284
00:17:45,840 --> 00:17:46,480
Has the chemistry professor

285
00:17:46,600 --> 00:17:48,080
replied to your email?

286
00:17:52,520 --> 00:17:54,440
What a pity!

287
00:17:57,000 --> 00:17:58,760
I'm not here to meet him anyway.

288
00:17:58,960 --> 00:18:00,440
